title: Liz Truss to lead trade mission to China next month | Anglia
text:
South West Norfolk MP Liz Truss is to visit China next month in her role as Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs.
She will visit Shanghai, Chengdu and Beijing to open new business links for the food and drink sector between the UK and China.
One visit will be to a microbrewery in Beijing to discuss key progress on exports of beer.
Last updated Tue 20 Oct 2015 Politics Norfolk Liz Truss
